"font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Measuring Innovation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The metrics used to measure national success in innovation could be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> co</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nsidered and compared across funding and rating bodies. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The NAO review notes that ‘R&amp;D is historically the most cited metric of innovation in an economy.’ </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Since innovation is not the same as development, it would be worthwhile</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> for the committee to consi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">der what metrics </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are appropriate for assessing the environment, and capacity, for innovation aside from R&amp;D spend, alongside how the UK performs internationally by these measures</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The abolishment of the UK R&amp;D Scoreboard has removed a key source of this in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">formation and the impact of this decision should be considered.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A further issue on R&amp;D intensity may be to investigate what the relative merits are of using R&amp;D intensity as a tool to compare