n></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Given that the intention of the Patent Box was to en</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">courage investment in research and innovation in the UK, we suggest that the committee investigate, at the earliest opportunity, what effect it has had (or is currently projected to have) upon innovation, and whether it is a successful tax incentive for en</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">couraging companies to undertake R&amp;D within the UK.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:113%; margin:5pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The UK has several mechanisms for supporting R&amp;D, in part by the Research Councils and in part by the Technology Strategy Board. The committee might like to understand how coherent the approaches of the v</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">arious agencies are, and what, if any, coherence and interaction exists with major European funding initiatives such as FP7 and Horizon 2020</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Research Concentration</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. The NAO report highlighted significant regional imbalance in levels of public and private R</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&amp;D funding. The committee</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> might wish to examine</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman